Model Year Start: 2019 Model: Prius Prod Date Range: [12/2018 -           ]
Title: EXTERIOR PANELS / TRIM: REAR BUMPER: REASSEMBLY; 2019 - 2022 MY Prius [12/2018 -        ]

REASSEMBLY

PROCEDURE

1. INSTALL REAR BUMPER ARM SUB-ASSEMBLY LH

(a) Install the rear bumper arm sub-assembly LH with the 4 bolts.

Torque:

18 N·m {184 kgf·cm, 13 ft·lbf}

2. INSTALL REAR BUMPER ARM SUB-ASSEMBLY RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

3. INSTALL NO. 1 REAR BUMPER REINFORCEMENT

(a) Install the No. 1 rear bumper reinforcement with the 6 bolts.

Torque:

34 N·m {347 kgf·cm, 25 ft·lbf}

4. INSTALL REAR BUMPER SIDE SEAL LH

(a) Install the 3 clips.

*1

Rear Bumper Side Clip

(b) Install the rear bumper side seal LH with the rear bumper side clip.

5. INSTALL REAR BUMPER SIDE SEAL RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

6. INSTALL REAR BUMPER SIDE RETAINER LH

(a) Engage the claw as shown in the illustration.

Install in this Direction (1)

Install in this Direction (2)

(b) Engage the guide as shown in the illustration.

(c) Engage the 3 clips as shown in the illustration to install the rear bumper side retainer LH.

Install in this Direction

7. INSTALL REAR BUMPER SIDE RETAINER RH

HINT:

Use the same procedure as for the LH side.

8. INSTALL CENTER REAR BUMPER PAD

HINT:

When installing the center rear bumper pad, heat the center rear bumper guard using a heat light.

Heating Temperature

Item

Temperature

Center Rear Bumper Guard

40 to 60°C (104 to 140°F)

CAUTION:

  • Do not touch the heat light and heated parts, touching the heat light may result in burns.
  • Touching heated parts for a long time may result in burns.

*a

Heated Part

*b

Heat Light

NOTICE:

Do not heat the center rear bumper guard excessively.

(a) Clean the center rear bumper guard surface.

(1) Using a heat light, heat the center rear bumper guard surface.

(2) Remove any remaining double-sided tape from the center rear bumper guard.

(3) Wipe off any tape adhesive residue with cleaner.

(b) Remove the release paper from a new center rear bumper pad.

HINT:

After removing the release paper, keep the exposed adhesive free from foreign matter.

(c) Install the center rear bumper pad as shown in the illustration.

HINT:

  • Install the center rear bumper pad along the line on the center rear bumper guard.
  • Press the center rear bumper pad firmly to install it.

*a

Line

9. INSTALL NO. 3 REAR BUMPER PAD

HINT:

  • Touching heated parts for a long time may result in burns.

*a

*b

Heat Light

(1) Using a heat light, heat the rear bumper cover surface.

(2) Remove any remaining double-sided tape from the rear bumper cover.

(3) Wipe off any tape adhesive residue with cleaner.

  • Use the same procedure for the RH side and LH side.

17. INSTALL ULTRASONIC SENSOR CLIP

HINT:

When installing the ultrasonic sensor clip, heat the rear bumper assembly using a heat light.

Heating Temperature

Item

Temperature

Rear Bumper Assembly

40 to 60°C (104 to 140°F)

CAUTION:

  • Do not touch the heat light and heated parts, touching the heat light may result in burns.
  • Touching heated parts for a long time may result in burns.

*a

Heated Part

*b

Heat Light

NOTICE:

Do not heat the rear bumper assembly excessively.

(a) Clean the rear bumper assembly surface.

(1) Using a heat light, heat the rear bumper assembly surface.

(2) Remove any remaining double-sided tape from the rear bumper assembly.

(3) Wipe off any tape adhesive residue with cleaner.

(b) Remove the release paper from each new ultrasonic sensor clip.

HINT:

After removing the release paper, keep the exposed adhesive free from foreign matter.

(c) w/o Intuitive Parking Assist System:

(1) Install the 2 ultrasonic sensor clips as shown in the illustration.

*a

Line

-

-

HINT:

  • Install the ultrasonic sensor clip along the line on the rear bumper assembly.
  • Press the ultrasonic sensor clip firmly to install it.

(d) w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System:

(1) Install the 6 ultrasonic sensor clips as shown in the illustration.

*a

Line

-

-

HINT:

  • Install the ultrasonic sensor clip along the line on the rear bumper assembly.
  • Press the ultrasonic sensor clip firmly to install it.

18. INSTALL NO. 3 LUGGAGE ROOM WIRE

(a) w/o Intuitive Parking Assist System:

(1) Engage the 10 clamps to install the No. 3 luggage room wire.

(b) w/ Intuitive Parking Assist System:

(1) Engage the 16 clamps to install the No. 3 luggage room wire.
